{"lemma":"زَنْجَبِيلُ","slug":"زَنْجَبِيلُ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"زَنْجَبِيلُ","root":"","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18217"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ginger","examples":[{"text":"وَيُسْقَوْنَ فِيهَا كَأْسًا كَانَ مِزَاجُهَا زَنْجَبِيلًا","english":"And they will be provided to drink a cup, the flavour/mixture of which is ginger."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nOld Tamil 𑀇𑀜𑁆𑀘𑀺 (iñci)\nProto-Dravidian *wēr\nOld Tamil 𑀯𑁂𑀭𑁆 (vēr)\nOld Tamil 𑀇𑀜𑁆𑀘𑀺𑀯𑁂𑀭𑁆 (iñcivēr)bor.\nSauraseni Prakrit 𑀲𑀺𑀁𑀕𑀺𑀯𑁂𑀭 (siṃgivera)der.\nMiddle Iranianbor.\nClassical Syriac ܙܢܓܒܝܠbor.\nArabic زنجبيل\nFrom Classical Syriac ܙܢܓܒܝܠ (zangabīl), ܙܢܓܒܝܪ (zangabīr), from Sauraseni Prakrit 𑀲𑀺𑀁𑀕𑀺𑀯𑁂𑀭 (siṃgivera), 𑀲𑀺𑀁𑀕𑀯𑁂𑀭 (siṃgavera), from Old Tamil 𑀇𑀜𑁆𑀘𑀺𑀯𑁂𑀭𑁆 (iñcivēr)."},"ipa":["/zan.d͡ʒa.biːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18217","headword_ar":"زَنْجَبِيلٌ","root":"znjbyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ginger; amomum zinziber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant growing in the country of the Arabs, in the land of 'Omán,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in El-Yemen also;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(accord. to different copies of the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creeping beneath the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"biting, to the tongue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing like the stalks of the papyrus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAsan","text_ar":"رَاسَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned below]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is no wild sort of it; nor is it a tree that is eaten fresh like as herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants, are eaten; but it is used in a dry state; and its conserve is the best of conserves; and the best thereof is what is brought from the country of the Zinj and China:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it has a property that is heating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warming, digestive, lenitive in a small degree, strengthening to the venereal faculty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clearing to the phlegm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpening to the intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and exhilarating:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if mixed with the moisture of the liver of the goat, and dried, and pulverized, and used as a collyrium, it removes the film"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and obscurity of the sight."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  It is mentioned in the Kur, where it is said, [lxxvi. 17 and 18,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna mizaAjuhaA zanojabiylFA EayonFA fiyhaA","text_ar":"كَانَ مِزَاجُهَا زَنْجَبِيلًا عَيْنًا فِيهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tusam~aY salosabiylFA","text_ar":"تُسَمَّى سَلْسَبِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The admixture whereof shall be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znjbyl","text_ar":"زنجبيل"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fountain therein named Selsebeel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e. it shall have the flavour of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znjbyl","text_ar":"زنجبيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ginger], which the Arabs esteem very pleasant: it may mean that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znjbyl","text_ar":"زنجبيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [essentially] in the wine of Paradise: or that it is the admixture thereof: or that it is a name for the fountain whence this wine is taken, and which is named Selsebeel also. (Az, O, TA.) As some assert, (ISd, TA,) it means also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine"},{"kind":"text","text":"[absolutely]. (S, ISd, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanojabiylu AlkilaAbi","text_ar":"زَنْجَبِيلُ الكِلَابِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, the leaves of which are like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAf","text_ar":"خِلَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salix Aegyptia"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the twigs are red: it clears the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discoloration of the face termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaf","text_ar":"كَلَف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spots in the skin termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nama$","text_ar":"نَمَش"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it kills dogs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) wherefore it is named in relation to them. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanojabiylu AlEajami","text_ar":"زَنْجَبِيلُ العَجَمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^u$oturogaAzu","text_ar":"الاُشْتُرْغَازُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a word of Persian origin, now applied by Arabs to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of carline thistle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [Accord. to Freytag,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Horminum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salvia silvestris:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this, I believe, is what is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^u$oturogaAn","text_ar":"اُشْتُرْغَان"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanojabiylu Al$~aAmi","text_ar":"زَنْجَبِيلُ الشَّامِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aAsanu","text_ar":"الرَّاسَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inula helenium, common inula,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elecampane"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["AHn","TA","S","K","ISd"]}]}}